title: The Internet Is Having A Riot Over Donald Trump's "Easy D" Tweet
text:
Trump might want to add "modern-day slang expert" to his list of advisers because he clearly does not know what "Easy D" means on the internet. (If he'd only brought TIFFANY to the White House with him, none of this would be happening!!!) You see, on Wednesday afternoon, he tweeted the following:
Big increase in traffic into our country from certain areas, while our people are far more vulnerable, as we wait for what should be EASY D!
— Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below It's not totally clear what Easy D means in his book, though it appears it stands for "Easy Decision," or maybe "Easy Directions"? No one really knows, but the internet was quick to point out what it stands for in the greater world:
Dude, if you want easy D, you can find it on Grindr. https://t.co/RiKdNVEOB7
— Josh Barro (@jbarro) February 8, 2017 Nobody said D was easy
No one ever said D would be this hard
— Molly Fitzpatrick (@mollyfitz) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Just think: somewhere right now, two White House staffers are discussing how to tell the President of the United States what "Easy D" means
— David Mack (@davidmackau) February 8, 2017 Easy D pic.twitter.com/YRIjsaSfkm
— DoSomething.org (@dosomething) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below . @realDonaldTrump Trust us. It's not all just "Easy D" pic.twitter.com/SY0zaJglI8
— corey kindberg (@coreykindberg) February 8, 2017 Ok "Easy D" time for today's post pic.twitter.com/nuze0t4cCZ
— Michelle (@IrishRose_14) February 8, 2017 America: land of the free, home of the easy D. https://t.co/pmW7YT3mKR
— Abby McDonald (@abbymcdonald) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Well, there's lots of ways to get easy d. pic.twitter.com/PxLhl4KNmJ
— Kryses/Wynfor @ WrA (@CasualFolami) February 8, 2017 can't believe POTUS is tweeting about the gay agenda: life, liberty, & the pursuit of EASY D https://t.co/1yMXX4lkQ5
— Tyler Oakley (@tyleroakley) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below The Easy D train is experiencing delays due to the diminishing parts of our government that are properly functioning as designed.
— Fake MTA (@FakeMTA) February 8, 2017 easy d pic.twitter.com/BX2nzpRnaF
— Trump Draws (@TrumpDraws) February 8, 2017 Easy D doesn't come for free, she's a real lady, and as for me, ha you’ll see, slam your body down and wind it all around, slam your body do
— bobby finger (@bobbyfinger) February 8, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Give me your tired, your poor, your huddled masses yearning for Easy D.
— Tyler Coates (@tylercoates) February 8, 2017 True story: Darryl McDaniels, who later cofounded Run-DMC, once styled himself as EASY D. pic.twitter.com/6elJdWlwRk
— Nate Silver (@NateSilver538) February 8, 2017 In conclusion, Donald "Easy D" Trump is officially now the president's new nickname:
GOP rapper names
Trump: Easy D
DeVos: Betsy Rick Ross
Spicer: Spice Cube
Sessions: The Notorious B.I.G.O.T.
Bannon: Bloatface Hitlah
— OhNoSheTwitnt (@OhNoSheTwitnt) February 8, 2017 Follow Diana on Twitter .
